118
00:11:04.640 --> 00:11:07.490
6.3.1 Glasses

119
00:11:07.490 --> 00:11:13.278
6.3.1.1 As is well known, we see the world through our eyes, not screens.

120
00:11:13.278 --> 00:11:17.715
If all the screens in the world went black, you still wouldn't be blind

121
00:11:17.715 --> 00:11:27.765
6.3.1.2 Therefore, the future's core interaction device must be glasses (not screens), which will replace phones/computers/all interaction endpoints

122
00:11:27.765 --> 00:11:34.778
6.3.1.3 Culturally, humanity has already accepted wearing glasses as an aesthetic choice.

123
00:11:34.778 --> 00:11:38.590
Unlike AI earpieces, which people think are ugly

124
00:11:38.590 --> 00:11:44.290
6.3.1.4 By the way, a widely circulated fallacy is robots

125
00:11:44.290 --> 00:11:47.753
a，The core of a humanoid robot is intimacy

126
00:11:47.753 --> 00:11:52.528
Not somersaults and other acrobatics; therefore its core is algorithms

127
00:11:52.528 --> 00:11:56.240
